  <prompt>
    Author `scripts/dataverse/Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1` modeled after existing `scripts/dataverse/Deploy-Playbook.ps1`. Seed 6 initial `sprk_playbookconsumer` records using the current production playbook GUIDs from existing env vars (`Workspace__*PlaybookId`). Idempotent UPSERT by alternate key `(consumertype + consumercode + environment)` — rerun is a no-op. Print env-var values BEFORE write for manual review. Document the script in `scripts/README.md`. After this task lands, downstream tasks 028c (Pattern A — 4 consumers) and 028d (Pattern B — 2 consumers) inject the routing service against a seeded table.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform Dataverse script author. Expert in PowerShell + PAC CLI + Dataverse Web API + idempotent UPSERT patterns by alternate key.</role>

  <goal>
    Running `Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1` against an empty Dev `sprk_playbookconsumer` table creates 6 records (matter-pre-fill, project-pre-fill, ai-summary, summarize-file, chat-summarize, email-analysis) using current env-var GUIDs. Rerun is a no-op — all 6 records detected by alternate key + skipped or update-no-change. Manual Dataverse view confirms 6 rows visible to admin. Script documented in `scripts/README.md`.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec §"Phase 1R" FR-1R-07. The 6 production-bound consumers today read playbook GUIDs from env vars (`Workspace__MatterPreFillPlaybookId`, etc.) — Phase 1R replaces this with Dataverse-backed routing. This seed script captures the current env-var values as the initial table contents so downstream consumer migrations (028c/028d) can swap reads from env-var to `IConsumerRoutingService.ResolveAsync` without behavior change. Documented full GUIDs in spec.md FR-1R-05 include `2d660cad-d418-f111-8343-7ced8d1dc988` (matter-pre-fill), `18cf3cc8-…` (ai-summary), `bc71facf-…` (email-analysis); the script reads `appsettings.json` + `appsettings.Development.json` as the AUTHORITATIVE source and prints values BEFORE write for manual review (defense against the 2026-06-24 UAT-2 failure mode).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>scripts/dataverse/Deploy-Playbook.ps1</file>
      <file>scripts/README.md</file>
      <file>src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.json</file>
