  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read `scripts/dataverse/Deploy-Playbook.ps1` end-to-end to match the existing pattern (auth, PAC CLI invocation, error handling, output formatting). Adopt the same shape for `Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1`.</step>
    <step order="2">Read `appsettings.json` + `appsettings.Development.json` to identify the 4 `Workspace__*PlaybookId` env-var keys (MatterPreFill, ProjectPreFill, AiSummary, Summarize) and their current values. For `chat-summarize`, resolve `summarize-document-for-chat@v1` by `sprk_playbookcode` at script execution time (PAC CLI query). For `email-analysis`, use the playbook GUID discovered in task 020.</step>
    <step order="3">Design the UPSERT-by-alternate-key flow — query `sprk_playbookconsumer` by `ak_consumertype_code_env`; if exists → update with same fields (no-op if values unchanged); if not → create. Use Dataverse Web API `Upsert` semantics (PATCH with alternate key URL) for atomicity.</step>
    <step order="4">Author `scripts/dataverse/Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1`. Parameters: `-EnvironmentUrl` (Dataverse env), `-AppSettingsPath` (default to `src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/appsettings.json`), `-DryRun` (print only, no write). Read 6 GUIDs from appsettings + chat-summarize playbookcode resolution + email-analysis GUID. PRINT all 6 (consumerType, consumerCode='default', playbookId, priority=500, environment='*') in a formatted table to stdout BEFORE write; require explicit confirmation OR `-Confirm:$false` flag to proceed.</step>
    <step order="5">Implement the UPSERT loop — for each of 6 records, query by alternate key; create or update with consumerType/consumerCode='default'/playbookId/priority=500/environment='*'/enabled=true/matchconditions=null. Log per-record outcome (created/updated-changed/updated-unchanged).</step>
    <step order="6">Test idempotency — run against empty Dev table → 6 records created; rerun immediately → 6 records detected, all updates skipped (no-op confirmed by log).</step>
    <step order="7">Update `scripts/README.md` with `Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1` section: purpose (FR-1R-07), prerequisites (Dataverse env auth, appsettings.json access), invocation example, expected output, idempotency guarantee.</step>
    <step order="8">Manual smoke — view 6 records in Power Apps maker portal as admin; confirm priority=500, environment='*', enabled=true, matchconditions=null, playbookId lookup populated.</step>
    <step order="9">Update TASK-INDEX.md: task 028b → ✅; current-task.md → ready for 028c + 028d (parallel-safe wave 1-M).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Deploy-Playbook.ps1, appsettings.json/Development.json, scripts/README.md</tool>
