  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1` exists at `scripts/dataverse/Seed-PlaybookConsumers.ps1`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Script reads 6 GUIDs from `appsettings.json` / `appsettings.Development.json` (not hardcoded) plus chat-summarize playbookcode lookup + email-analysis GUID from task 020.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Script PRINTS all 6 consumer rows BEFORE write; supports `-DryRun` flag for print-only.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Running against empty table creates 6 records (matter-pre-fill, project-pre-fill, ai-summary, summarize-file, chat-summarize, email-analysis) — all with consumerCode='default', priority=500, environment='*', enabled=true, matchconditions=null.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Rerunning is idempotent — log confirms 6 records detected via alternate key + zero changes.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Manual Dataverse view confirms 6 rows visible to admin with correct playbookId lookups.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`scripts/README.md` documents the script (purpose, prerequisites, invocation, output, idempotency).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    The print-before-write step is the binding defense against the 2026-06-24 UAT-2 failure mode (env var set under legacy key). If any env-var value looks wrong (e.g., null, malformed GUID, mismatched with known production), STOP and escalate to owner before writing. Email-analysis GUID is the one discovered during task 020 — re-confirm the value against `notes/handoffs/020-*` evidence before script execution. Chat-summarize must resolve via playbookcode lookup at script execution time (NOT hardcoded), because the playbook GUID is environment-specific.
  </notes>

